    Development Description

      Advertisement
      These captivating and private 1, 2, 3 and 4 bedroom apartments in the heart of city life will open your eyes to what living in comfort truly means in The Elysian, an ultramodern apartment complex that boasts Cork’s tallest residential tower. Wake up to incredible views from masterfully styled interiors that accommodate modern tastes in a variety of ways. Sunlight fills generous windows, creating bright and comfortable living spaces, highlighting the flawless design detail and finish. Most residences gaze upon tranquil Japanese gardens where nature looks her best. Large decked balconies or winter gardens bring the beauty of Cork home, giving you opportunities to admire the scenery that surrounds this spectacular complex. A dedicated onsite concierge is at your service seven days a week. Available from 8am to 11pm, this property service takes care of package deliveries, requests and more, along with maintaining the privacy and safety of the grounds. Private onsite amenities offer you freedom to take life at your own pace. There is a stylish business suite so you can work from home in comfort, along with a residents’ fully equipped gym, entertaining kitchen and lounge space for when you want to switch off or socialise. Join a community of nature enthusiasts, culture fans, health buffs and pleasure seekers who enjoy a five star living experience in stunning surroundings. Virtual tours enable you to view apartments while respecting social distancing guidelines. They are helpful in illustrating the layout and interior style of a sample residence.

      Location

      The Elysian takes pride of place in the heart of Cork with 211 apartments that afford residents new opportunities to enjoy the cosmopolitan vibe of this true city of culture. Before you explore the city, you have the convenience of Aldi and The Bookshelf Café onsite, ensuring your kitchen is always well stocked. You can stroll to the South Mall, just 600 metres away, and admire some of the original Georgian houses that line this street while you enjoy a coffee on the terrace of the Imperial Hotel. Great eateries, cafés and bars are peppered throughout the city centre, just waiting to be discovered. Patrick Street, around the corner from the South Mall, is only 700 metres from The Elysian, giving you easy access to the cream of cultural attractions such as Cork Opera House, Crawford Art Gallery and Opera Lane, the home of style enthusiasts. The renowned English Market, one of the city’s treasures with its entrance on Grand Parade, is sheer bliss for connoisseurs of good food, offering you the finest local produce. If you like staying near the Marina, you can enjoy food and crafts at Marina Market every weekend on Centre Park Road, or a leisurely walk along Marina Way to Blackrock Castle and village, only two kilometres away. You can admire the greenery of nearby Kennedy Park, which is merely a 10-minute walk away on Victoria Road, giving you plenty of recreational space. Travelling beyond the city is easy with Kent railway station just one kilometre from The Elysian, and the South Link Road outside your door, connecting you with Cork International Airport and the M8 motorway.
